{"session_id": 47, "bill_id": 13952, "bill_type": "House Bill", "bill_number": 1305, "bill_title": "to provide rule-making authority to the Gaming Commission to establish the number of employees required on a premises with limited card games and slot machines.", "sponsors": [{"legislator_profile_id": 2121, "is_prime": true}, {"legislator_profile_id": 2146, "is_prime": true}, {"legislator_profile_id": 2096, "is_prime": false}, {"legislator_profile_id": 2136, "is_prime": false}, {"legislator_profile_id": 2142, "is_prime": false}, {"legislator_profile_id": 2150, "is_prime": false}, {"legislator_profile_id": 2161, "is_prime": false}, {"legislator_profile_id": 2182, "is_prime": false}, {"legislator_profile_id": 2189, "is_prime": false}], "keywords": ["Electronic Surveillance", "Gaming (See also Video Lottery)", "Labor & Employment"], "audio": [], "bill_versions": [{"bill_id": 13952, "bill_version_id": 77609, "bill_version": "Introduced", "bill_version_date": "1998-01-26T00:00:00-06:00", "bill_text": "FOR AN ACT ENTITLED, An Act to provide rule-making authority to the Gaming Commission to establish the number of employees required on a premises with limited card games and slot machines. BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA: Section 1. That \u00a7 42-7B-40 be amended to read as follows: 42-7B-40. Any retail licensee under this chapter shall have at least one licensed employee that is at least twenty-one years of age on the premises and within in full view and control of any limited card games or slot machines operated on the premises pursuant to the license obtained . The commission shall adopt rules, pursuant to chapter 1-26, to establish the number of employees required to monitor the premises. The rules may authorize the use of electronic devices or other types of monitoring equipment. 750 copies of this document were printed by the South Dakota Legislative Research Council at a cost of $.016 per page. . Insertions into existing statutes are indicated by underscores. Deletions from existing statutes are indicated by overstrikes."}, {"bill_id": 13952, "bill_version_id": 77608, "bill_version": "House State Affairs Engrossed", "bill_version_date": "1998-02-11T00:00:00-06:00", "bill_text": "FOR AN ACT ENTITLED, An Act to provide rule-making authority to the Gaming Commission to establish the number of employees required on a premises with limited card games and slot machines. BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA: Section 1. That \u00a7 42-7B-40 be amended to read as follows: 42-7B-40. Any retail licensee under this chapter shall have at least one licensed employee that is at least twenty-one years of age on the premises and or within a contiguous premises in full view and control of any limited card games or slot machines operated on the premises pursuant to the license obtained . The commission shall adopt rules, pursuant to chapter 1-26, to establish the number of employees required to monitor the premises. The rules may also authorize the use of electronic devices or other types of monitoring equipment. BILL HISTORY 1/26/98 First read in House and referred to State Affairs. H.J. 229 2/9/98 Scheduled for Committee hearing on this date. 2/11/98 Scheduled for Committee hearing on this date. 2/11/98 State Affairs Do Pass Amended, Passed, AYES 12, NAYS 1."}, {"bill_id": 13952, "bill_version_id": 77607, "bill_version": "Enrolled", "bill_version_date": "1998-02-20T10:10:35-06:00", "bill_text": ""}], "amendments": [], "fiscal_notes": [], "action_log": [{"bill_id": 13952, "action_date": "1998-01-26T14:00:00-06:00", "document_id": 76901, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/76901.pdf", "status_text": "First read in House and referred to", "journal_page": 229, "committee_id_action": 600, "committee_id_assigned": 595, "result": "N", "vote": {}}, {"bill_id": 13952, "action_date": "1998-02-09T10:00:00-06:00", "document_id": 76688, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegisla